# Excludes for `railway up`. Railway honours this in addition to .gitignore.
# .gitignore already excludes node_modules, .yarn caches, dist, build, etc.
#
# IMPORTANT: every entry under packages/ in package.json `workspaces` MUST be
# uploaded — yarn install requires each workspace's package.json. Excluding
# any whole package breaks transitive type/dev dep resolution and the docker
# build fails (e.g. @types/lodash.camelcase missing for twenty-shared).
#
# We drop the .git history (~385 MB) and large static asset directories that
# the server/worker docker build doesn't need (docs images, marketing site
# public assets). Each workspace's package.json + src + scripts stays.

.git
.github
.idea
.vscode
*.log

# Big static assets not used by the server/worker docker build.
packages/twenty-docs/images
packages/twenty-docs/l
packages/twenty-website/public
packages/twenty-website-new/public
